WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.220 --> 00:00:04.898
<i>Previously on</i> Prison Break:

2
00:00:04.922 --> 00:00:06.299
I'm looking for someone. A
guy named Lincoln Burrows.

3
00:00:06.323 --> 00:00:07.750
<i>Man killed the Vice
President's brother.</i>

4
00:00:07.774 --> 00:00:09.636
Why you want to see
Burrows so bad anyhow?

5
00:00:09.660 --> 00:00:10.926
<i>Because he's my brother.</i>

6
00:00:10.995 --> 00:00:12.739
I'm getting you out of
here. It's impossible.

7
00:00:12.763 --> 00:00:14.891
Not if you designed
the place. it isn't.

8
00:00:14.915 --> 00:00:17.477
You've seen the
blueprints. Better than that.

9
00:00:17.501 --> 00:00:18.583
I've got them on me.

10
00:00:19.820 --> 00:00:23.071
<i>Nick Savrinn. As of
now. both of you are dead.</i>

11
00:00:24.525 --> 00:00:27.058
This is Bellick. Our
wing has been breached.

12
00:00:27.127 --> 00:00:28.610
Marilyn. no!

13
00:00:28.679 --> 00:00:32.363
The chair isn't the only way
to take a man's life in prison.

14
00:00:32.432 --> 00:00:33.432
What are you doing?

15
00:00:33.484 --> 00:00:34.661
Your father's
already in trouble.

16
00:00:34.685 --> 00:00:35.962
There's nothing
we can do about it.

17
00:00:35.986 --> 00:00:36.986
Come on!

18
00:00:37.053 --> 00:00:38.403
My first assignments on PI.

19
00:00:38.472 --> 00:00:40.539
we were up here
cleaning out toxic mold.

20
00:00:40.607 --> 00:00:41.807
PI didn't go there.

21
00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:44.020
We'd never assign
inmates to do that.

22
00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:45.660
Tyler Robert.

23
00:00:45.729 --> 00:00:47.529
This here must be your daughter.

24
00:00:48.766 --> 00:00:50.982
It's over. We don't
need him no more.

25
00:00:51.051 --> 00:00:52.433
You're not gonna kill him.

26
00:00:57.474 --> 00:00:59.124
One for the team.

27
00:01:04.114 --> 00:01:05.725
<i>Seventeen days from now.</i>

28
00:01:05.749 --> 00:01:08.383
<i>they strap my brother
to an electric chair.</i>

29
00:01:10.654 --> 00:01:13.054
<i>send 50.000 volts
coursing through his body</i>

30
00:01:13.123 --> 00:01:15.089
<i>for a crime he didn't commit.</i>

31
00:01:16.393 --> 00:01:18.927
<i>I'm here to make sure
that doesn't happen.</i>

32
00:01:22.900 --> 00:01:26.234
<i>I've been in Fox River
nearly three weeks now.</i>

33
00:01:26.303 --> 00:01:28.748
<i>In that time. I've managed
to get out the back of my cell</i>

34
00:01:28.772 --> 00:01:32.307
<i>and into the old steam pipes
that run beneath the prison.</i>

35
00:01:33.410 --> 00:01:36.110
<i>Those pipes are our way out.</i>

36
00:01:38.181 --> 00:01:41.783
Think of this place
like it's a map of the US.

37
00:01:41.851 --> 00:01:44.686
Our cell over there.
that's New York City.

38
00:01:45.823 --> 00:01:48.423
Infirmary. our exit.
that's California.

39
00:01:48.492 --> 00:01:51.009
The pipes beneath our
feet that connect the two...

40
00:01:51.077 --> 00:01:52.327
Route 66.

41
00:01:52.395 --> 00:01:55.263
Route 66. Our
ticket out of here.

42
00:01:55.332 --> 00:01:57.043
I assume we're
doing this at night.

43
00:01:57.067 --> 00:01:58.567
That's right.

44
00:01:58.635 --> 00:02:02.738
We're locked up. Fish.
and your boy is in solitary.

45
00:02:02.806 --> 00:02:05.206
How we just gonna
fly out of our cages

46
00:02:05.275 --> 00:02:06.591
and right into your cell.

47
00:02:06.660 --> 00:02:08.076
right into New York City?

48
00:02:08.145 --> 00:02:09.277
You're not.

49
00:02:10.213 --> 00:02:12.581
You're gonna meet me halfway.

50
00:02:12.650 --> 00:02:13.782
In St. Louis.

51
00:02:13.850 --> 00:02:16.367
Route 66 runs directly
beneath that building.

52
00:02:16.436 --> 00:02:19.204
It's the only building sitting
on top of those tunnels.

53
00:02:19.272 --> 00:02:21.673
All we gotta do is
get in there on PI

54
00:02:21.742 --> 00:02:23.925
and dig ourselves an on-ramp.

55
00:02:24.861 --> 00:02:26.761
Shortly after we
hit the infirmary.

56
00:02:26.830 --> 00:02:28.764
Then we'll be
outside those walls.

57
00:02:28.832 --> 00:02:30.432
What's in there?

58
00:02:30.500 --> 00:02:31.884
It's an old storage room.

59
00:02:31.936 --> 00:02:34.269
<i>I figure John here can
pull all the strings he needs.</i>

60
00:02:34.354 --> 00:02:37.154
<i>It's not that easy. Fish.
That's a restricted area.</i>

61
00:02:38.559 --> 00:02:41.042
I got to be able to justify
it to the bulls. you know.

62
00:02:41.111 --> 00:02:43.271
There's gotta be some
actual work to be done in there

63
00:02:43.297 --> 00:02:44.846
for me to get in
there. You follow?

64
00:02:44.915 --> 00:02:46.648
Then you better figure it out.

65
00:02:46.716 --> 00:02:48.667
'Cause if we don't
get in that room.

66
00:02:48.736 --> 00:02:50.668
we're not getting out of here.

67
00:02:50.737 --> 00:02:52.854
I'm feeling kind of left out.

68
00:02:53.907 --> 00:02:56.675
New York.
California. St. Louis...

69
00:02:56.744 --> 00:02:58.126
What are we discussing?

70
00:02:58.194 --> 00:02:59.922
Talking baseball. actually.

71
00:02:59.946 --> 00:03:01.496
Huh.

72
00:03:01.564 --> 00:03:04.482
Now. that's a subject I just
happen to know quite a bit about.

73
00:03:04.551 --> 00:03:07.335
What a shame. The
conversation's over.

74
00:03:07.404 --> 00:03:10.622
Really. now. that any
way to treat a teammate?

75
00:03:15.262 --> 00:03:17.190
I'm coming along
on this endeavor

76
00:03:17.214 --> 00:03:19.464
whether you like it or not.

77
00:03:19.533 --> 00:03:22.751
'Cause I got a hell of a
singing voice otherwise.

78
00:03:25.539 --> 00:03:27.605
I won't take that
piece of crap along.

79
00:03:27.674 --> 00:03:28.740
I won't do it.

80
00:03:28.808 --> 00:03:30.142
Me. neither.

81
00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:31.976
We won't have to.

82
00:03:32.046 --> 00:03:35.006
He'll be out of the
picture soon enough.

83
00:03:37.067 --> 00:03:39.735
The state provides
$25.000 insurance.

84
00:03:39.803 --> 00:03:43.005
Plus donations from the Illinois
Corrections Officers' Foundation.

85
00:03:43.090 --> 00:03:46.341
That's the last thing on
my mind right now. Warden.

86
00:03:48.062 --> 00:03:49.694
Do you know who killed him?

87
00:03:49.763 --> 00:03:51.279
We have some leads.

88
00:03:52.182 --> 00:03:53.881
But I can promise you this.

89
00:03:53.950 --> 00:03:57.235
We are not going to rest until
we find out what happened.

90
00:03:58.138 --> 00:04:00.205
His pictures are missing.

91
00:04:00.274 --> 00:04:03.075
He had a photo of
our daughter in here.

92
00:04:05.662 --> 00:04:07.562
Not to worry. We'll find them.

93
00:04:11.252 --> 00:04:14.135
I begged him not
to take this job.

94
00:04:14.854 --> 00:04:17.772
Shauna. I am so sorry.

95
00:04:21.194 --> 00:04:23.078
I'll walk you to your car.

96
00:04:24.364 --> 00:04:27.232
Captain. I need to speak
with you for a second.

97
00:04:27.301 --> 00:04:29.095
I'll meet you in the hallway.

98
00:04:32.789 --> 00:04:35.707
I want the son of
a bitch who did this.

99
00:04:35.776 --> 00:04:39.260
Now. you do whatever
you need to do to find him.

100
00:04:39.329 --> 00:04:40.862
You understand?

101
00:04:47.137 --> 00:04:49.938
We have five boxes.
Wanna give me a hand?

102
00:04:51.424 --> 00:04:53.608
Veronica.

103
00:04:53.677 --> 00:04:55.455
That phone call was
textbook scare tactics.

104
00:04:55.479 --> 00:04:56.995
That's what they want.

105
00:04:57.064 --> 00:04:58.908
They want to scare us from
doing what they know we can do.

106
00:04:58.932 --> 00:04:59.964
And what's that?

107
00:05:00.033 --> 00:05:01.282
Expose them.

108
00:05:01.351 --> 00:05:03.234
This guy bothering you
again. Miss Donovan?

109
00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:05.653
No. Lukasz. The other
night was my fault.

110
00:05:05.722 --> 00:05:07.055
It was a misunderstanding.

111
00:05:07.124 --> 00:05:09.508
Okay. But if you
need anything...

112
00:05:09.576 --> 00:05:11.927
Trust me. You'll be
the first person I call.

113
00:05:13.246 --> 00:05:15.313
Here. Let me.

114
00:05:19.486 --> 00:05:23.154
Those boxes contain seven
years of criminal appellate work.

115
00:05:23.223 --> 00:05:25.490
If there's a precedent
in there somewhere

116
00:05:25.559 --> 00:05:27.559
that can help us suspend
Lincoln's execution.

117
00:05:27.627 --> 00:05:29.394
we're gonna find it.

118
00:05:29.462 --> 00:05:32.058
You can just leave those by
the door. Lukasz. I'll bring them in.

119
00:05:32.082 --> 00:05:35.150
Oh. that's okay. I've
got your key right here.

120
00:05:35.219 --> 00:05:38.436
If I didn't know better. I would
say Lukasz was sweet on you.

121
00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:39.755
Very funny.

122
00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:47.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

123
00:06:29.423 --> 00:06:30.600
Fire.

124
00:06:30.624 --> 00:06:31.656
What?

125
00:06:31.725 --> 00:06:33.758
Fire. We burn the place down.

126
00:06:33.827 --> 00:06:35.321
How's that gonna help us?

127
00:06:35.345 --> 00:06:37.462
A few years ago. the
chapel burned down.

128
00:06:37.531 --> 00:06:41.165
and the D.O.C. realized
they had some toxic issues.

129
00:06:41.234 --> 00:06:44.002
You know. asbestos.
lead paint. you name it.

130
00:06:44.071 --> 00:06:45.820
They couldn't find a contractor.

131
00:06:45.889 --> 00:06:48.039
so they put the
inmates on the job.

132
00:06:48.108 --> 00:06:51.042
We spent like five. six
hours in there at a time.

133
00:06:51.110 --> 00:06:55.179
But the good news is. no
guards came around almost at all.

134
00:06:56.266 --> 00:06:58.144
Can you get us in there?

135
00:06:58.168 --> 00:07:00.719
Been doing a
little. uh. thinking.

136
00:07:06.793 --> 00:07:09.360
I'm gonna need
a PI card. aren't I?

137
00:07:12.282 --> 00:07:14.749
I mean. that's where this
whole thing is happening.

138
00:07:14.818 --> 00:07:16.550
isn't it?

139
00:07:16.619 --> 00:07:18.269
It's on its way.

140
00:07:21.191 --> 00:07:23.111
You're slow-walking
me. aren't you?

141
00:07:23.143 --> 00:07:24.687
Why would I do such a thing?

142
00:07:24.711 --> 00:07:26.739
You think Bellick's gonna pop me

143
00:07:26.763 --> 00:07:29.123
for shanking that CO. Bob.

144
00:07:30.066 --> 00:07:31.594
Maybe you'll take a little walk

145
00:07:31.618 --> 00:07:32.862
and tell him for
yourself. right?

146
00:07:32.886 --> 00:07:35.237
And I'll be out of
your hair for good.

147
00:07:35.305 --> 00:07:37.872
Well. I got news for you.

148
00:07:37.941 --> 00:07:41.153
If I go down for killing
Bob. believe me.

149
00:07:41.177 --> 00:07:44.278
I'm gonna take a
little walk of my own.

150
00:07:44.347 --> 00:07:47.883
Tell them about that hole
you got behind your toilet.

151
00:07:51.138 --> 00:07:52.237
So.

152
00:07:53.673 --> 00:07:55.833
how about that PI card?

153
00:07:58.695 --> 00:07:59.772
I don't know if you remember.

154
00:07:59.796 --> 00:08:01.595
but that summer
before fifth grade.

155
00:08:01.664 --> 00:08:03.831
when I stayed with
you a couple weeks.

156
00:08:03.900 --> 00:08:06.867
and you thought I broke
your glass coffee table?

157
00:08:06.937 --> 00:08:08.136
Uh-huh.

158
00:08:09.306 --> 00:08:11.439
And when you came
home. I denied it.

159
00:08:12.508 --> 00:08:14.208
But you told me

160
00:08:15.979 --> 00:08:18.029
you could care less
about the coffee table.

161
00:08:18.098 --> 00:08:20.698
you just didn't want
me lying to you.

162
00:08:20.767 --> 00:08:22.567
And you said I'd
feel a lot better

163
00:08:22.635 --> 00:08:25.337
if I just told you the truth.

164
00:08:25.405 --> 00:08:27.839
and you promised
not to be angry.

165
00:08:27.908 --> 00:08:29.257
I remember.

166
00:08:30.844 --> 00:08:32.277
Well. I broke it.

167
00:08:34.380 --> 00:08:35.630
I know.

168
00:08:38.435 --> 00:08:40.318
You know. if there's anything

169
00:08:40.386 --> 00:08:42.636
that you want to
get off of your chest.

170
00:08:42.705 --> 00:08:44.005
you can tell me.

171
00:08:44.074 --> 00:08:46.458
and I promise I won't get angry.

172
00:08:46.526 --> 00:08:48.726
You want to know
if I killed that guy?

173
00:08:53.216 --> 00:08:57.385
I. uh. went there planning
to do something wrong.

174
00:09:00.523 --> 00:09:02.752
But I didn't kill that guy.

175
00:09:02.776 --> 00:09:05.626
Someone's working hard
to make it look like I did.

176
00:09:05.712 --> 00:09:09.797
Anyway. there's a chance
the execution may not happen.

177
00:09:09.866 --> 00:09:10.882
What?

178
00:09:10.951 --> 00:09:12.751
Veronica's working my case.

179
00:09:12.819 --> 00:09:14.397
and I got a reporter
coming today

180
00:09:14.421 --> 00:09:16.721
who actually
believes I'm innocent.

181
00:09:17.624 --> 00:09:19.374
So I ain't dead yet.

182
00:09:20.410 --> 00:09:23.077
LJ. look at me.

183
00:09:24.264 --> 00:09:25.996
You gotta have faith. kid.

184
00:09:27.184 --> 00:09:29.200
Just have a little faith.

185
00:09:40.113 --> 00:09:41.124
Kellerman.

186
00:09:41.148 --> 00:09:42.196
Well?

187
00:09:42.265 --> 00:09:43.276
<i>Taken care of.</i>

188
00:09:43.300 --> 00:09:44.348
Good.

189
00:09:44.418 --> 00:09:46.551
Now move on to the second thing.

190
00:09:46.620 --> 00:09:48.386
If you could see
what we're looking at.

191
00:09:48.455 --> 00:09:50.366
believe me. Burrows is
gonna get the message.

192
00:09:50.390 --> 00:09:52.823
Which is what you've
assured me of before.

193
00:09:52.892 --> 00:09:55.943
Yet that message keeps
getting returned to sender.

194
00:09:56.013 --> 00:09:59.147
<i>Now move on the second
thing. and report back.</i>

195
00:09:59.216 --> 00:10:01.599
We're headed there now.

196
00:10:01.668 --> 00:10:03.279
You're thinking too much.

197
00:10:03.303 --> 00:10:05.152
Yeah. God forbid.

198
00:10:11.244 --> 00:10:13.138
He's gonna toss
every cell in this block

199
00:10:13.162 --> 00:10:14.529
until he finds the killer.

200
00:10:14.598 --> 00:10:16.047
If he tosses this one.

201
00:10:16.116 --> 00:10:18.077
he's going to find the hole
back there in a heartbeat.

202
00:10:18.101 --> 00:10:19.334
I know.

203
00:10:20.870 --> 00:10:22.419
We gotta turn T-Bag in.

204
00:10:22.488 --> 00:10:23.821
That's the only way it'll stop.

205
00:10:23.890 --> 00:10:26.007
We turn him in. he'll talk.

206
00:10:31.081 --> 00:10:33.464
So we're screwed
either way. aren't we?

207
00:10:40.390 --> 00:10:42.290
Which one? Right there.

208
00:10:42.358 --> 00:10:44.191
St. Louis.

209
00:11:08.234 --> 00:11:10.179
What the hell are
you doing here?

210
00:11:10.203 --> 00:11:12.119
Clean-up detail. We
thought this was storage.

211
00:11:12.188 --> 00:11:14.150
Does this look like
storage to you. you idiot?

212
00:11:14.174 --> 00:11:15.506
It's a restricted area.

213
00:11:15.575 --> 00:11:17.655
This is a CO break
room. Now. back it up.

214
00:11:18.679 --> 00:11:19.944
Back it up now!

215
00:11:20.013 --> 00:11:21.496
Sorry. Officer.

216
00:11:21.565 --> 00:11:22.997
Won't happen again.

217
00:11:37.431 --> 00:11:40.565
A freaking break room?
Are you kidding me?

218
00:11:40.633 --> 00:11:42.793
They must've changed
it since the retrofit.

219
00:11:42.835 --> 00:11:44.196
The bulls are
camped out in there.

220
00:11:44.220 --> 00:11:45.381
They'll never leave.

221
00:11:45.405 --> 00:11:47.572
You got a back-up
plan? There isn't one.

222
00:11:47.640 --> 00:11:49.402
It's the only room
sitting on top of that pipe.

223
00:11:49.426 --> 00:11:51.570
It's the only way out. and
we gotta get back in there.

224
00:11:51.594 --> 00:11:52.811
Impossible. Fish.

225
00:11:52.879 --> 00:11:54.919
Maybe not. Check it out.

226
00:11:58.851 --> 00:11:59.912
I don't get it.

227
00:11:59.936 --> 00:12:01.296
How come they let him
into the guards' room?

228
00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:02.470
He's a trustee.

229
00:12:02.539 --> 00:12:04.150
The ones with the
highest security clearance.

230
00:12:04.174 --> 00:12:05.968
But why him? He can be trusted.

231
00:12:05.992 --> 00:12:07.620
How does one become a trustee?

232
00:12:07.644 --> 00:12:10.178
Just have a spotless
record for the last 30 years.

233
00:12:10.247 --> 00:12:11.890
Pretty much
counts all of us out.

234
00:12:11.914 --> 00:12:14.131
Which means we've
got to get him onboard.

235
00:12:14.200 --> 00:12:16.617
Forget it. The
guy's a boy scout.

236
00:12:23.042 --> 00:12:24.775
Mr. Westmoreland.

237
00:12:25.579 --> 00:12:27.112
Hey. Michael.

238
00:12:28.648 --> 00:12:30.014
You found your cat yet?

239
00:12:30.083 --> 00:12:31.916
Still MIA.

240
00:12:33.987 --> 00:12:35.064
You can always get another.

241
00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:37.672
I don't want another.

242
00:12:37.741 --> 00:12:39.473
Besides. it's a moot point.

243
00:12:39.542 --> 00:12:40.958
She was grandfathered.

244
00:12:41.027 --> 00:12:43.410
Once she's gone. no more pets.

245
00:12:43.479 --> 00:12:45.680
Wouldn't be an issue if
you were on the outside.

246
00:12:47.300 --> 00:12:49.420
Still tugging on that leash. eh?

247
00:12:49.452 --> 00:12:51.836
Yep.

248
00:12:51.905 --> 00:12:55.151
And this is the part where
I extend a formal invitation.

249
00:12:55.175 --> 00:12:57.202
'Cause you still
think I'm D.B. Cooper.

250
00:12:57.226 --> 00:12:59.360
I don't think. I know.

251
00:13:01.381 --> 00:13:02.581
The way I see it.

252
00:13:02.649 --> 00:13:04.360
you're in here doing 60-to-life

253
00:13:04.384 --> 00:13:05.894
for a vehicular manslaughter.

254
00:13:05.918 --> 00:13:07.285
It would've been 20.

255
00:13:07.354 --> 00:13:09.632
but the car you
were in was stolen.

256
00:13:09.656 --> 00:13:12.123
Felony murder rule
cubes up your sentence.

257
00:13:12.192 --> 00:13:13.958
and here you are.

258
00:13:14.027 --> 00:13:16.347
Hitting that woman
was an accident.

259
00:13:16.395 --> 00:13:18.029
But the car?

260
00:13:18.098 --> 00:13:20.258
No one accidentally
steals a car.

261
00:13:20.950 --> 00:13:22.249
So the question is.

262
00:13:22.335 --> 00:13:23.918
why would Charles Westmoreland

263
00:13:23.987 --> 00:13:25.736
<i>be in Arizona boosting a car.</i>

264
00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:27.583
<i>10 states away
from where he lived.</i>

265
00:13:27.607 --> 00:13:30.007
<i>and only 10 miles away
from the Mexican border?</i>

266
00:13:30.059 --> 00:13:33.594
<i>And why. two days before that.
would someone make a phone call</i>

267
00:13:33.663 --> 00:13:36.648
<i>to his wife from a
motel in Portland.</i>

268
00:13:36.716 --> 00:13:38.561
<i>a stone's throw
away from the airport</i>

269
00:13:38.585 --> 00:13:40.451
<i>out of which. shortly after.</i>

270
00:13:40.519 --> 00:13:44.389
Flight 305 was hijacked
by one D.B. Cooper.

271
00:13:44.457 --> 00:13:46.251
Seven hours after the hijacking.

272
00:13:46.275 --> 00:13:47.954
records show
Charles Westmoreland

273
00:13:47.978 --> 00:13:49.438
was treated for a busted knee

274
00:13:49.462 --> 00:13:51.373
<i>at a free clinic
in Brigham City.</i>

275
00:13:51.397 --> 00:13:53.325
Only way to get from
Portland. Oregon.

276
00:13:53.349 --> 00:13:55.394
to Brigham City.
Utah in seven hours.

277
00:13:55.418 --> 00:13:56.867
<i>is in a car.</i>

278
00:13:56.936 --> 00:13:59.982
<i>breaking every land-speed
record known to man.</i>

279
00:14:00.006 --> 00:14:01.405
<i>or flying.</i>

280
00:14:01.474 --> 00:14:04.125
It's public record D.B.
Cooper jumped out of that 727

281
00:14:04.193 --> 00:14:06.461
about an hour after takeoff.

282
00:14:06.529 --> 00:14:08.479
Taking a dive at 10.000 feet

283
00:14:08.548 --> 00:14:12.550
with $1.5 million in cash and
a hastily packed parachute

284
00:14:12.619 --> 00:14:15.036
might make for a
pretty rough landing.

285
00:14:15.104 --> 00:14:17.138
Rough enough to
shatter some bones.

286
00:14:17.206 --> 00:14:18.806
Maybe even a left knee.

287
00:14:20.627 --> 00:14:22.071
D.B. Cooper would've had a car

288
00:14:22.095 --> 00:14:23.539
waiting for him when he landed.

289
00:14:23.563 --> 00:14:25.996
According to D.M.V.
records. in 1971.

290
00:14:26.065 --> 00:14:30.167
Charles Westmoreland was the
proud owner of a '65 Chevy Nova.

291
00:14:30.237 --> 00:14:32.803
As it happens. a '65 Chevy Nova

292
00:14:32.872 --> 00:14:34.789
<i>with the registration
number scraped off</i>

293
00:14:34.858 --> 00:14:36.619
<i>was found abandoned
with a blown gasket</i>

294
00:14:36.643 --> 00:14:38.860
<i>along the Arizona border</i>

295
00:14:38.928 --> 00:14:42.580
<i>a mile or two away from where
you accidentally hit that woman</i>

296
00:14:42.649 --> 00:14:44.198
with your stolen car.

297
00:14:47.420 --> 00:14:48.803
Interesting story.

298
00:14:48.872 --> 00:14:50.438
Interesting man.

299
00:14:52.558 --> 00:14:54.041
But you didn't answer one thing.

300
00:14:54.110 --> 00:14:55.660
What's that?

301
00:14:57.546 --> 00:15:01.949
Maybe I did hurt my
knee. I did steal that car.

302
00:15:02.018 --> 00:15:04.535
and I did accidentally
hit that poor lady.

303
00:15:05.638 --> 00:15:07.822
But how could I
have hijacked a plane

304
00:15:07.890 --> 00:15:10.224
in Portland on November 24th.

305
00:15:10.293 --> 00:15:11.692
when I was in Folsom.

306
00:15:11.761 --> 00:15:14.378
finishing up a 30-day
drunk and disorderly?

307
00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:22.904
I hope you aren't hanging this
whole escape on that money.

308
00:15:22.972 --> 00:15:25.006
'cause I'm not the
one in possession of it.

309
00:15:29.279 --> 00:15:31.545
Thanks for the invite. though.

310
00:15:47.213 --> 00:15:48.512
Veronica.

311
00:15:52.151 --> 00:15:53.951
Veronica. come on.

312
00:15:58.757 --> 00:16:00.240
We're okay.

313
00:16:01.277 --> 00:16:02.804
How is this okay. Nick?

314
00:16:02.828 --> 00:16:04.490
Somebody just tried to kill us.

315
00:16:04.514 --> 00:16:06.864
I know. I was there.
Then act like it. okay?

316
00:16:06.916 --> 00:16:10.196
We just watched a man burn
to death right in front of us.

317
00:16:11.954 --> 00:16:13.237
My God.

318
00:16:15.407 --> 00:16:17.174
Lukasz. My God.

319
00:16:17.243 --> 00:16:18.876
It's okay. it's okay.

320
00:16:18.945 --> 00:16:20.611
We just left him there.

321
00:16:21.714 --> 00:16:23.075
There was nothing
we could do for him.

322
00:16:23.099 --> 00:16:25.866
He was dead as soon
as he opened the door.

323
00:16:25.935 --> 00:16:28.452
I am trying so hard to
understand all this. Nick.

324
00:16:28.521 --> 00:16:30.148
Who these people
are. what they want.

325
00:16:30.172 --> 00:16:31.617
How we just walked
away from there

326
00:16:31.641 --> 00:16:33.018
without even calling the police.

327
00:16:33.042 --> 00:16:34.837
We did it because these
people we're dealing with

328
00:16:34.861 --> 00:16:36.961
won't stop until we're dead.

329
00:16:37.029 --> 00:16:39.024
Now. if they think we're
dead. like they do right now.

330
00:16:39.048 --> 00:16:40.426
maybe we get a little
breathing room here.

331
00:16:40.450 --> 00:16:41.760
We figure out what
our next move is.

332
00:16:41.784 --> 00:16:43.329
No. we should go to the police.

333
00:16:43.353 --> 00:16:45.747
I've been telling myself the
same thing. But you know what?

334
00:16:45.771 --> 00:16:47.271
They're bigger than the police.

335
00:16:50.743 --> 00:16:53.277
Now. we go to the authorities.
and all we're gonna be doing.

336
00:16:53.346 --> 00:16:55.107
is broadcasting to
them that we're still alive

337
00:16:55.131 --> 00:16:57.965
and then we got their target
right on our backs again.

338
00:16:58.668 --> 00:17:00.334
We can't hide forever.

339
00:17:01.404 --> 00:17:04.405
No. no. maybe
not forever. But I...

340
00:17:04.473 --> 00:17:07.074
I think I know a place we
can. at least for a little while.

341
00:17:12.148 --> 00:17:14.392
We'll just have to go
in there ourselves then.

342
00:17:14.416 --> 00:17:17.184
Like I said. unless the old
man's in. it's not possible.

343
00:17:17.253 --> 00:17:19.098
And even if it were.
with the guards in there.

344
00:17:19.122 --> 00:17:20.766
there's no way in hell
they're just gonna sit back

345
00:17:20.790 --> 00:17:22.322
and watch us start a fire.

346
00:17:22.391 --> 00:17:25.551
See. I already figured that
part out. I've been thinking.

347
00:17:25.995 --> 00:17:27.161
And?

348
00:17:27.229 --> 00:17:29.024
That thing you're doing
at the Pope's office.

349
00:17:29.048 --> 00:17:30.876
you're using rubber
cement? Yeah.

350
00:17:30.900 --> 00:17:33.061
Can you get some out
of there? Maybe. Why?

351
00:17:33.085 --> 00:17:36.120
Look. there's a coffee maker
in the guards' room. right?

352
00:17:36.172 --> 00:17:39.201
I got a hook-up with one
of my boys in the kitchen.

353
00:17:39.225 --> 00:17:42.193
If we can get rubber cement
in the bottom of that coffee pot.

354
00:17:42.261 --> 00:17:44.328
when the burner goes on...

355
00:17:46.733 --> 00:17:48.633
It's a good idea.

356
00:17:48.701 --> 00:17:52.303
But without Westmoreland.
we're never getting in that room.

357
00:17:52.371 --> 00:17:54.683
He doesn't want any
part of the escape? No.

358
00:17:54.707 --> 00:17:57.975
Well. what does he want?
He's gotta want something.

359
00:17:58.895 --> 00:18:00.978
Everybody wants something.

360
00:18:09.055 --> 00:18:12.439
Come on. kitty. Come on.

361
00:18:13.842 --> 00:18:16.526
Here. kitty. kitty. kitty.

362
00:18:16.595 --> 00:18:18.879
Yes. that's a good girl.

363
00:18:20.015 --> 00:18:21.248
Come on.

364
00:18:26.940 --> 00:18:28.672
I don't believe it.

365
00:18:30.910 --> 00:18:32.959
Thank you. You're welcome.

366
00:18:33.028 --> 00:18:34.428
Where'd you find her?

367
00:18:34.497 --> 00:18:36.113
In the yard. By the chapel.

368
00:18:37.800 --> 00:18:39.800
Why do I get the feeling

369
00:18:39.869 --> 00:18:41.847
there's a string
attached to this?

370
00:18:41.871 --> 00:18:44.071
Not a string. Just a favor.

371
00:18:47.977 --> 00:18:52.145
I'm not D.B. Cooper.
That's all right.

372
00:18:52.214 --> 00:18:55.916
'Cause it's not gonna take D.B.
Cooper to do what I need done.

373
00:18:55.985 --> 00:18:57.818
What's that?

374
00:18:57.887 --> 00:18:59.519
All I want you to do

375
00:18:59.589 --> 00:19:03.223
is take a certain coffee pot into
the guard room at a certain time

376
00:19:03.292 --> 00:19:05.125
and turn the burner on.

377
00:19:05.194 --> 00:19:06.994
Why?

378
00:19:07.063 --> 00:19:09.496
Let's just say it'd be in
everyone's best interest

379
00:19:09.565 --> 00:19:11.632
if a fire were
to start in there.

380
00:19:11.700 --> 00:19:14.902
Marilyn. did you think
he was the arsonist type?

381
00:19:16.038 --> 00:19:19.506
I'm not. I'm the
clean-up crew type.

382
00:19:19.575 --> 00:19:22.760
The type that gets
access to all kinds of tools.

383
00:19:24.964 --> 00:19:28.999
Michael. I'm grateful
for this. I really am.

384
00:19:29.068 --> 00:19:31.313
But I've made it a point
to keep my nose clean

385
00:19:31.337 --> 00:19:33.315
ever since I walked
into this place.

386
00:19:33.339 --> 00:19:35.973
32 years without a blemish.

387
00:19:36.042 --> 00:19:39.877
If that parole board date
ever comes. I want to be ready.

388
00:19:39.945 --> 00:19:41.912
I can't jeopardize that.

389
00:19:42.515 --> 00:19:43.547
Sorry.

390
00:19:48.922 --> 00:19:50.103
Michael.

391
00:19:51.373 --> 00:19:53.174
Thanks. though. Really.

392
00:19:58.280 --> 00:20:00.014
After what you went
through in the riot.

393
00:20:00.083 --> 00:20:01.849
I thought you
might take a day off.

394
00:20:01.918 --> 00:20:04.151
I'm fine.

395
00:20:04.220 --> 00:20:07.321
I couldn't find anybody
to cover for me anyway.

396
00:20:09.658 --> 00:20:12.126
I hope you don't feel
like you owe me anything.

397
00:20:13.062 --> 00:20:15.730
I do. I'm. uh...

398
00:20:18.501 --> 00:20:21.102
I really appreciate
what you did for me.

399
00:20:26.326 --> 00:20:27.475
But?

400
00:20:31.063 --> 00:20:35.966
But you told me that you had
been up in the crawlspace for PI.

401
00:20:36.035 --> 00:20:37.735
and...

402
00:20:37.804 --> 00:20:39.904
PI was never
assigned to go there.

403
00:20:45.094 --> 00:20:47.278
We're done here. right?

404
00:20:47.346 --> 00:20:49.291
Michael. don't be like that.

405
00:20:49.315 --> 00:20:51.635
I just want some answers.

406
00:20:52.268 --> 00:20:53.600
Thanks for the shot. Doc.

407
00:20:57.956 --> 00:20:59.973
Sue Parsons. <i>Headline Press.</i>

408
00:21:00.960 --> 00:21:02.192
Thanks for coming by.

409
00:21:02.261 --> 00:21:04.044
I appreciate your
taking the time.

410
00:21:04.112 --> 00:21:06.313
Appreciate you
looking into my case.

411
00:21:06.382 --> 00:21:09.449
So. what can you tell me?
From what I understand.

412
00:21:09.518 --> 00:21:12.652
you have numerous people
working on your behalf as we speak.

413
00:21:12.721 --> 00:21:13.881
Yeah. um...

414
00:21:13.923 --> 00:21:16.690
Well. Veronica Donovan.
She's my attorney.

415
00:21:16.759 --> 00:21:18.041
And Nick Savrinn.

416
00:21:18.110 --> 00:21:21.928
He works at Project
Justice. Savrinn.

417
00:21:21.997 --> 00:21:24.565
Okay. Have they gotten very far?

418
00:21:24.650 --> 00:21:27.334
Nothing to go to court
with. Not yet. anyway.

419
00:21:29.221 --> 00:21:31.922
You ever think it's
just time to let go?

420
00:21:31.991 --> 00:21:33.958
Accept what happened?

421
00:21:34.026 --> 00:21:35.625
Let go. yeah.

422
00:21:35.694 --> 00:21:37.878
Accept what happened. never.

423
00:21:37.946 --> 00:21:40.230
I mean. would you. if
someone had set you up.

424
00:21:40.299 --> 00:21:42.333
destroyed your life?

425
00:21:42.402 --> 00:21:45.168
I guess I'm thinking in
terms of the pain and anguish

426
00:21:45.237 --> 00:21:47.637
it's caused your
friends and loved ones.

427
00:21:47.706 --> 00:21:49.940
People who care about
me. they believe me.

428
00:21:50.009 --> 00:21:53.293
That's all that matters to
me right now. That's all I got.

429
00:21:53.362 --> 00:21:56.847
You have a son.
Lincoln. Jr.. LJ.

430
00:21:57.399 --> 00:21:58.766
Yeah. Why?

431
00:21:58.851 --> 00:22:02.720
I have a source that tells me
if you accept what happened.

432
00:22:02.789 --> 00:22:04.455
and stop fighting
your execution.

433
00:22:04.524 --> 00:22:06.239
your son will be
left out of this.

434
00:22:06.308 --> 00:22:07.574
If not.

435
00:22:07.643 --> 00:22:09.226
I hope you said goodbye to him

436
00:22:09.294 --> 00:22:11.395
when he left here this morning.

437
00:22:11.464 --> 00:22:14.582
Who are you? One
Burrows is gonna die.

438
00:22:14.650 --> 00:22:16.083
Up to you which one.

439
00:22:16.169 --> 00:22:18.830
Who are you? Who are you?

440
00:22:18.854 --> 00:22:21.756
Hey. don't let her go!
She threatened my son!

441
00:22:21.824 --> 00:22:24.108
Please. no! She
threatened my son.

442
00:22:24.177 --> 00:22:25.743
No!

443
00:22:36.205 --> 00:22:37.388
LJ Burrows?

444
00:22:37.456 --> 00:22:38.689
Yeah.

445
00:22:38.757 --> 00:22:41.108
I'm Officer Hale
with juvenile court.

446
00:22:41.176 --> 00:22:43.221
We just need to do a quick
survey of the residence.

447
00:22:43.245 --> 00:22:44.995
Make sure the
environment here is reflective

448
00:22:45.064 --> 00:22:46.724
of the terms of your probation.

449
00:22:46.748 --> 00:22:47.942
Your parents home?

450
00:22:47.966 --> 00:22:51.118
No. But they'll be
home any minute.

451
00:22:51.187 --> 00:22:54.455
Well. then. I can get started.

452
00:22:57.109 --> 00:22:58.158
LJ and his dad.

453
00:22:58.227 --> 00:22:59.904
you never said how
it went this morning.

454
00:22:59.928 --> 00:23:01.561
Sounded fine.

455
00:23:01.630 --> 00:23:04.025
Of course. everything a 15-year-old
boy tells his mother is fine.

456
00:23:04.049 --> 00:23:05.110
Look. no offense.

457
00:23:05.134 --> 00:23:06.912
but can I see some
kind of identification?

458
00:23:06.936 --> 00:23:07.936
Sure.

459
00:23:07.970 --> 00:23:09.253
LJ. we're home.

460
00:23:12.574 --> 00:23:14.191
LJ. you here?

461
00:23:19.965 --> 00:23:21.298
Oh. my God.

462
00:23:21.350 --> 00:23:22.833
Drop the phone. lady.

463
00:23:22.902 --> 00:23:24.797
This is the only
warning I'm giving you.

464
00:23:24.821 --> 00:23:26.086
Drop it.

465
00:23:28.207 --> 00:23:29.339
Run!

466
00:23:29.825 --> 00:23:31.341
LJ. go!

467
00:23:45.640 --> 00:23:48.575
Pick up. Pick up. please.

468
00:23:48.643 --> 00:23:50.077
Please answer. Come on.

469
00:23:53.900 --> 00:23:54.832
LJ.

470
00:23:54.901 --> 00:23:57.221
We're not here to hurt you.

471
00:24:01.107 --> 00:24:02.506
Wh-Whoa.

472
00:24:02.575 --> 00:24:07.461
911. Send.

473
00:24:07.530 --> 00:24:09.946
You really think you're
gonna get to four buttons

474
00:24:10.015 --> 00:24:11.815
before I get to one?

475
00:24:16.372 --> 00:24:17.637
Come on.

476
00:24:20.058 --> 00:24:22.109
LJ. get out of here!

477
00:24:33.072 --> 00:24:34.237
Mom.

478
00:25:02.518 --> 00:25:03.728
<i>Where are you going. LJ?</i>

479
00:25:03.752 --> 00:25:05.352
What do you want from me?

480
00:25:05.420 --> 00:25:07.171
Cooperation. that's all.

481
00:25:07.239 --> 00:25:09.072
<i>You want cooperation?</i>

482
00:25:09.141 --> 00:25:11.525
I know what you look
like. you son of a bitch!

483
00:25:11.593 --> 00:25:13.176
I'm going to the police.

484
00:25:13.245 --> 00:25:16.241
Going to the police. I don't
think that's such a good idea. LJ.

485
00:25:16.265 --> 00:25:19.166
I mean. with your prints on
the murder weapon and all.

486
00:25:19.235 --> 00:25:20.879
I didn't touch the
murder weapon.

487
00:25:20.903 --> 00:25:22.202
<i>Of course you didn't.</i>

488
00:25:22.270 --> 00:25:25.221
I know that and you know that.

489
00:25:26.442 --> 00:25:28.322
I just don't think you're
gonna have much luck

490
00:25:28.377 --> 00:25:30.126
convincing Ballistics of that.

491
00:25:30.195 --> 00:25:31.611
Who the hell are you people?

492
00:25:31.697 --> 00:25:33.446
Just concerned neighbors.

493
00:25:33.515 --> 00:25:36.216
We heard a bit of a
ruckus at the Rix's house.

494
00:25:36.285 --> 00:25:39.052
Gosh. you know. I guess we
really should've seen it coming.

495
00:25:39.121 --> 00:25:40.720
I mean. all the
signs were there.

496
00:25:40.789 --> 00:25:43.023
drug use. decline in
academic performance.

497
00:25:43.092 --> 00:25:45.259
But we didn't think he'd
ever do something like this.

498
00:25:45.327 --> 00:25:46.471
No one's gonna believe that.

499
00:25:46.495 --> 00:25:47.778
<i>Yes. they will.</i>

500
00:25:47.830 --> 00:25:50.163
And when they catch you.
and they will catch you. LJ.

501
00:25:50.232 --> 00:25:51.693
<i>they're gonna try
you as an adult.</i>

502
00:25:51.717 --> 00:25:53.216
<i>You know what that means.</i>

503
00:25:53.285 --> 00:25:55.986
We can help you. LJ.
We're the only hope you got.

504
00:25:56.038 --> 00:25:57.038
No. you're not.

505
00:26:07.116 --> 00:26:09.466
She made that choice. not you.

506
00:26:10.902 --> 00:26:12.519
Let's find the kid.

507
00:26:19.511 --> 00:26:21.378
You got Marilyn back.

508
00:26:22.281 --> 00:26:24.081
Sure did.

509
00:26:24.149 --> 00:26:25.382
That's good.

510
00:26:28.153 --> 00:26:30.955
How long ago you quit smoking?

511
00:26:31.023 --> 00:26:32.856
A little over nine years now.

512
00:26:32.925 --> 00:26:34.335
You don't mind. do you?

513
00:26:44.971 --> 00:26:47.404
Feel a kinship
with you. Charles.

514
00:26:52.344 --> 00:26:55.128
More than any other con here.

515
00:26:55.197 --> 00:26:57.647
And we've seen
a lot. haven't we?

516
00:26:58.717 --> 00:26:59.900
Sure have.

517
00:27:01.086 --> 00:27:03.286
And correct me if I'm wrong.

518
00:27:04.606 --> 00:27:06.851
but I've always
treated you fair.

519
00:27:06.875 --> 00:27:09.426
I've always
appreciated that fact.

520
00:27:10.946 --> 00:27:13.781
I've known Bob since
he was 18 years old.

521
00:27:16.519 --> 00:27:18.318
I got him this job.

522
00:27:20.022 --> 00:27:22.923
You can imagine
how responsible I feel.

523
00:27:22.991 --> 00:27:24.958
I can't help you
with that. boss.

524
00:27:25.027 --> 00:27:27.043
I think you can.

525
00:27:27.112 --> 00:27:30.314
Word is he died
in front of your cell.

526
00:27:30.383 --> 00:27:33.350
<i>And you were right
here when it happened.</i>

527
00:27:38.274 --> 00:27:41.408
We've both been around
long enough to know

528
00:27:41.476 --> 00:27:45.012
that when a con starts
that snitching business.

529
00:27:45.080 --> 00:27:48.248
he's not long for this world.

530
00:27:48.317 --> 00:27:50.250
Don't put me in
that position. boss.

531
00:27:57.677 --> 00:28:01.344
If you don't tell
me who killed Bob

532
00:28:01.413 --> 00:28:03.446
before I leave this cell.

533
00:28:05.350 --> 00:28:07.710
our friendship goes with it.

534
00:28:16.111 --> 00:28:17.360
That's a nice cat.

535
00:28:24.887 --> 00:28:28.127
Westmoreland knows.
and his jaw ain't that strong.

536
00:29:15.604 --> 00:29:17.237
What's this?

537
00:29:18.440 --> 00:29:19.739
Nothing.

538
00:29:20.909 --> 00:29:22.542
You stalker.

539
00:29:22.628 --> 00:29:24.911
I'm not a stalker. I just...

540
00:29:26.648 --> 00:29:27.728
I don't get it.

541
00:29:27.782 --> 00:29:29.916
What is there to get?

542
00:29:29.985 --> 00:29:32.285
He doesn't fit the profile.

543
00:29:32.354 --> 00:29:33.971
Right? The man's
got a graduate degree.

544
00:29:34.023 --> 00:29:36.823
He lives in my neighborhood.

545
00:29:36.892 --> 00:29:38.519
Guys like that hang
out in Streeterville.

546
00:29:38.543 --> 00:29:39.977
they drink single malt Scotch.

547
00:29:40.045 --> 00:29:41.428
they pay $200 for Cubs tickets.

548
00:29:41.496 --> 00:29:42.529
They don't rob banks.

549
00:29:42.598 --> 00:29:44.814
Maybe he couldn't
afford season tickets.

550
00:29:44.883 --> 00:29:47.550
Maybe that's why
he robbed the bank.

551
00:29:47.619 --> 00:29:50.187
Thank you. I'm
actually being serious.

552
00:29:50.239 --> 00:29:51.605
Can I ask you something?

553
00:29:51.673 --> 00:29:52.673
Yeah.

554
00:29:53.692 --> 00:29:55.442
Why do you care so much?

555
00:29:55.511 --> 00:29:57.744
'Cause he lied to me.

556
00:29:57.813 --> 00:29:59.613
They all lie to you.

557
00:30:05.471 --> 00:30:07.182
Maybe because he's
the one guy in here

558
00:30:07.206 --> 00:30:08.805
I can actually get to.

559
00:30:09.975 --> 00:30:13.559
One guy I can make
a difference with.

560
00:30:15.881 --> 00:30:17.430
Go home. girl.

561
00:30:17.499 --> 00:30:19.733
You keep burning it
at both ends like this.

562
00:30:19.801 --> 00:30:22.435
you're gonna
drive yourself crazy.

563
00:30:23.805 --> 00:30:25.171
Good night.

564
00:30:28.910 --> 00:30:30.827
<i>I'm sorry. Burrows.</i>

565
00:30:30.896 --> 00:30:33.447
Both of them were dead by the
time the paramedics got there.

566
00:30:35.834 --> 00:30:37.028
What about my son?

567
00:30:37.052 --> 00:30:38.969
He's missing.

568
00:30:39.037 --> 00:30:41.287
The police are treating
him as a fugitive.

569
00:30:42.524 --> 00:30:43.890
A fugitive?

570
00:30:43.959 --> 00:30:46.560
They found his prints
on the murder weapon.

571
00:30:47.463 --> 00:30:49.529
It's impossible.

572
00:30:49.598 --> 00:30:50.631
I. uh...

573
00:30:50.699 --> 00:30:52.582
I need to call him.

574
00:30:52.634 --> 00:30:55.230
No. I can't do that. What do
you mean you can't do that?

575
00:30:55.254 --> 00:30:57.365
His life's in danger!
Look. Burrows!

576
00:30:57.389 --> 00:30:58.989
The police have instructed me

577
00:30:59.058 --> 00:31:00.840
that this is an
ongoing investigation.

578
00:31:00.909 --> 00:31:04.327
And as such. any contact
you make with your son

579
00:31:04.396 --> 00:31:07.865
could potentially aid
and abet him as a fugitive.

580
00:31:10.952 --> 00:31:12.035
I'm sorry.

581
00:31:12.654 --> 00:31:14.872
Warden. please!

582
00:31:19.778 --> 00:31:21.411
Front gate open!

583
00:31:33.509 --> 00:31:35.008
Let's go. man.

584
00:31:36.595 --> 00:31:38.345
That's messed up. man.

585
00:31:38.413 --> 00:31:39.980
Jeez. do he even know?

586
00:31:40.048 --> 00:31:41.747
I don't think so.

587
00:31:41.816 --> 00:31:43.216
Man. here he is.

588
00:32:17.169 --> 00:32:18.635
What's up. T?

589
00:32:20.939 --> 00:32:22.806
We family. right?

590
00:32:24.559 --> 00:32:26.860
Hell. yeah. we are.

591
00:32:26.929 --> 00:32:29.979
Well. I'm in a quandary.
and I need your help.

592
00:32:31.583 --> 00:32:32.833
Name it.

593
00:32:32.901 --> 00:32:35.102
Bellick's squeezing tighter
and tighter around here.

594
00:32:35.170 --> 00:32:39.388
And you were right. Eventually.
somebody's mouth is gonna start moving.

595
00:32:39.441 --> 00:32:45.128
Thing is. Trokey. if I get popped
for this. what with my priors.

596
00:32:45.197 --> 00:32:48.097
and predisposition
to violent behavior.

597
00:32:50.235 --> 00:32:52.552
I'll spend the rest
of my life in the SHU.

598
00:32:52.620 --> 00:32:56.422
But if you come forward

599
00:32:56.491 --> 00:33:00.794
with only your drug convictions
and a whole lot of remorse...

600
00:33:00.862 --> 00:33:02.740
I can't do that. T.
I ain't finished yet.

601
00:33:02.764 --> 00:33:05.093
No need. I ain't going
down for murdering no hack.

602
00:33:05.117 --> 00:33:07.797
I mean. you understand
that. don't you?

603
00:33:08.420 --> 00:33:10.580
You ain't mad. are you?

604
00:33:13.425 --> 00:33:16.059
No. Trokey. I'm not mad.

605
00:34:37.292 --> 00:34:39.776
I need out. I gotta find him.

606
00:34:39.844 --> 00:34:42.345
You will. Both of us. Soon.

607
00:34:42.414 --> 00:34:44.208
They're coming after
my family. Michael.

608
00:34:44.232 --> 00:34:45.531
You've gotta trust me.

609
00:34:45.617 --> 00:34:47.777
We're gonna get this
done. "Get this done."

610
00:34:47.803 --> 00:34:50.170
How? Tell me. Michael. tell me.

611
00:34:50.239 --> 00:34:51.838
You can't. can you?

612
00:34:51.907 --> 00:34:54.853
I gotta get out of here
now. LJ's in trouble.

613
00:34:54.877 --> 00:34:57.493
Scofield. Now how about it?

614
00:34:58.613 --> 00:35:00.379
Just stick with me.

615
00:35:11.225 --> 00:35:13.242
Yo. Bruce! Hey!

616
00:35:14.780 --> 00:35:16.346
What's up. bro?

617
00:35:40.838 --> 00:35:42.984
If you go out there.
they will gun you down.

618
00:35:43.008 --> 00:35:44.274
I don't care anymore.

619
00:35:44.342 --> 00:35:46.621
Well. you better start thinking
about what you're doing.

620
00:35:46.645 --> 00:35:48.356
Because you can't
help LJ if you're dead.

621
00:35:48.380 --> 00:35:51.181
What the hell's
going on in here?

622
00:35:51.249 --> 00:35:52.777
We got a problem? No.

623
00:35:52.801 --> 00:35:54.441
Well. then get on your feet.

624
00:35:54.502 --> 00:35:56.330
Let's go. CO: There's a fire!

625
00:35:57.956 --> 00:35:59.155
Son of a...

626
00:35:59.224 --> 00:36:02.291
What the hell's going
on in Building 2? Come in.

627
00:36:02.360 --> 00:36:04.544
<i>Fire in the CO break room.</i>

628
00:36:26.234 --> 00:36:28.668
Thanks. I didn't do it for you.

629
00:36:37.612 --> 00:36:40.813
Found the source. Someone
in here smoke these?

630
00:36:41.650 --> 00:36:43.049
Bilsons?

631
00:36:44.252 --> 00:36:45.502
Bellick.

632
00:36:47.422 --> 00:36:49.889
Captain Bellick. got
someone to see you.

633
00:36:52.444 --> 00:36:55.061
What the hell do you want?

634
00:36:55.130 --> 00:36:57.296
I know who killed Bob. sir.

635
00:37:22.824 --> 00:37:24.357
I don't know how that got there.

636
00:37:27.095 --> 00:37:30.229
It's a mock. A mock!
You set me up! Let's go.

637
00:37:30.298 --> 00:37:32.209
Bad enough you killed a guard.

638
00:37:32.233 --> 00:37:34.395
Don't try to lay it off
on somebody else now.

639
00:37:34.419 --> 00:37:37.237
You set me up! He set me up!

640
00:37:51.169 --> 00:37:52.368
Wow.

641
00:37:52.437 --> 00:37:54.248
Your father lived here? Yeah.

642
00:37:54.272 --> 00:37:57.307
He wanted someplace that
was completely off the grid.

643
00:37:57.375 --> 00:37:59.976
A place the government
didn't even know existed.

644
00:38:00.045 --> 00:38:01.555
He tapped into the power lines.

645
00:38:01.579 --> 00:38:03.779
A well supplies the
place with water.

646
00:38:03.848 --> 00:38:07.233
Last few years of his life he
barely even left the property.

647
00:38:07.302 --> 00:38:09.486
It's... Yeah.

648
00:38:09.554 --> 00:38:12.705
When you spend so many years
fighting cops and prosecutors and judges

649
00:38:12.774 --> 00:38:15.475
trying to take your freedom
for something you didn't do.

650
00:38:15.543 --> 00:38:20.045
you used every cent you had in
attorney's fees. you wind up losing anyway.

651
00:38:22.267 --> 00:38:24.627
Fifteen years of his life.

652
00:38:26.354 --> 00:38:28.788
almost all of his
son's childhood.

653
00:38:31.459 --> 00:38:36.512
I guess I can forgive him for
wanting to hide away. be left alone.

654
00:38:36.581 --> 00:38:39.349
We'll be safe here until
we figure out our next move.

655
00:38:46.474 --> 00:38:49.191
Hey. hold up here a
minute. Hold up here.

656
00:38:49.260 --> 00:38:51.138
There seems to be
a bit of confusion.

657
00:38:51.162 --> 00:38:53.530
I-I'm supposed
to be on this detail.

658
00:38:53.598 --> 00:38:55.231
I don't think so.

659
00:38:55.733 --> 00:38:58.184
Oh. John.

660
00:38:58.252 --> 00:39:00.619
You can't be serious.

661
00:39:00.706 --> 00:39:04.974
Not after our long illustrious
history we shared together.

662
00:39:05.042 --> 00:39:08.694
All those nights
in New York City.

663
00:39:09.630 --> 00:39:11.247
In California.

664
00:39:13.418 --> 00:39:16.001
In St. Louis.

665
00:39:16.070 --> 00:39:18.821
They were good times.
weren't they. John?

666
00:39:20.258 --> 00:39:22.220
Tell the badge here about them.

667
00:39:22.244 --> 00:39:24.604
'Cause if you don't want to.

668
00:39:25.230 --> 00:39:26.446
I certainly could.

669
00:39:38.777 --> 00:39:40.459
I want this place gutted.

670
00:39:40.528 --> 00:39:42.106
The drywall's gotta be torn out.

671
00:39:42.130 --> 00:39:43.591
The studs gotta be removed.

672
00:39:43.615 --> 00:39:45.748
Boss. we got some
toxic issues here.

673
00:39:45.817 --> 00:39:47.900
Asbestos. to start with.

674
00:39:47.969 --> 00:39:49.536
Take it up with the union.

675
00:39:49.621 --> 00:39:52.500
All I'm saying is. this room
is your only priority now.

676
00:39:52.524 --> 00:39:55.169
It better be brand spanking
new when you're done.

677
00:39:55.193 --> 00:39:57.154
If anybody's thinking
about getting cute.

678
00:39:57.178 --> 00:40:00.379
trying to trunk one of
these tools out of here.

679
00:40:00.448 --> 00:40:03.848
Brady's got the outline of every
single piece of hardware in here.

680
00:40:03.885 --> 00:40:07.270
And at the end of every day.
every single piece better match up.

681
00:40:07.339 --> 00:40:09.622
or you're all going to the hole.

682
00:40:23.788 --> 00:40:25.071
Let's go.

683
00:40:32.113 --> 00:40:33.812
This goes down four feet.

684
00:40:33.882 --> 00:40:35.882
It connects to the
main line below.

685
00:40:35.951 --> 00:40:37.550
All we gotta do is widen it.

686
00:40:37.618 --> 00:40:40.269
and we've got ourselves
an on-ramp to Route 66.

687
00:40:46.778 --> 00:40:48.244
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

688
00:40:48.313 --> 00:40:49.674
They're gonna hear this. man.

689
00:40:49.698 --> 00:40:50.698
They won't.

690
00:41:01.626 --> 00:41:03.866
Come on. pretty. We a team now.

691
00:41:13.872 --> 00:41:15.387
Best get cracking. eh?

692
00:41:15.456 --> 00:41:16.555
You. shut up.

693
00:41:35.677 --> 00:41:37.588
You really think you're
gonna get to four buttons

694
00:41:37.612 --> 00:41:38.812
before I get to one?

695
00:41:59.700 --> 00:42:01.801
I don't have my glasses.

696
00:42:01.870 --> 00:42:04.437
How 'bout you read this for me?

697
00:42:04.506 --> 00:42:07.856
Tell me the news. The
latest developments.

698
00:42:07.925 --> 00:42:09.925
Evidently. there
was an explosion

699
00:42:09.994 --> 00:42:12.544
in a Gold Coast apartment
in Chicago yesterday.

700
00:42:12.614 --> 00:42:15.592
Gas line. Everyone
inside was killed.

701
00:42:15.616 --> 00:42:17.666
Shame. Anything else?

702
00:42:17.735 --> 00:42:19.652
How about that
kid up in Oak Park?

703
00:42:19.721 --> 00:42:21.421
The one they say
killed his parents.

704
00:42:21.489 --> 00:42:23.155
Oh. they got him. They did?

705
00:42:23.224 --> 00:42:25.625
He's in custody. Good.

706
00:42:25.694 --> 00:42:27.726
I imagine heads would've rolled

707
00:42:27.795 --> 00:42:29.862
if he hadn't been caught.

708
00:42:29.931 --> 00:42:31.965
Lives would've been lost.

709
00:42:33.134 --> 00:42:34.934
How about you
hand that back to me?

710
00:42:35.003 --> 00:42:36.970
Now that it's yesterday's news.

711
00:42:37.038 --> 00:42:39.172
we can put it
behind us. can't we?

712
00:42:40.408 --> 00:42:44.143
Move on to the next
chapter of our lives.

713
00:42:46.381 --> 00:42:49.548
You're not just doing
this for me. you know.

714
00:42:49.617 --> 00:42:51.316
Or my brother.

715
00:42:51.385 --> 00:42:52.818
Yes?

716
00:42:52.887 --> 00:42:56.656
They're ready for you.
Madam Vice President.

717
00:42:56.724 --> 00:42:59.692
You're doing it
for your country.

718
00:43:06.434 --> 00:43:07.945
Madam Vice President.

719
00:43:07.969 --> 00:43:09.513
Madam Vice President.
a question. please.

720
00:43:09.537 --> 00:43:11.186
Madam Vice President.

720
00:43:12.305 --> 00:44:12.282
